article.headline: E. Kentucky 85, Tennessee Tech 80
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Joshua Jones scored a career-high 25 points to lead Eastern Kentucky to an 85-80 win over Tennessee Tech Saturday night. The Colonels (9-7, 3-3 Ohio Valley Conference) connected on 12 3-pointers -- including eight in the second half -- to pull away from the Golden Eagles down the stretch. Tennessee Tech (8-7, 2-3) forced four ties and six lead changes and made seven 3-pointers in the second half to stay within striking distance of the Colonels. Mike Rose scored 18 points for Eastern Kentucky. Josh Taylor chipped in with 13, including nine in the last five minutes to help seal the deal for the Colonels. Justin Stommes added 12. Tennessee Tech's Frank Davis led his team with 24 points. Will Barnes followed Davis with 11 points, and Bassey Inameti had 10. Davis made seven 3-pointers for the Golden Eagles.
